    "Thomas Manton": "Again, they rejoice because they pass into glory more swiftly. The enemies do them a favor by removing them from a troublesome world. This made the early Christians rejoice more when they were condemned than when they were absolved. They kissed the stake and thanked the executioner because of their earnest desires to be with Christ. So Justin Martyr writes, \u201cWe thank you for delivering us from hard taskmasters, that we may more sweetly enjoy the presence of Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ.\u201d Objection\n18. Again, they rejoice because they pass into glory more swiftly. The enemies do them a favor by removing them from a troublesome world. This made the early Christians rejoice more when they were condemned than when they were absolved. They kissed the stake and thanked the executioner because of their earnest desires to be with Christ. So Justin Martyr writes, \u201cWe thank you for delivering us from hard taskmasters, that we may more sweetly enjoy the presence of Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` Christ.\u201d Objection",
    "Unknown": "Because there is wrath, to wit, conceived by God against thee. Because by thy pleading the cause of the wicked, thou hast deserved that God should give sentence against thee, as was now said, and hast provoked God\u2019s wrath against thee; therefore look to thyself, and reconcile thyself to God by true repentance whilst thou mayst, and before sentence be executed upon thee. Beware: this is not in the Hebrew, but is necessarily to be understood to make up the sense, and is oft understood in the like [v_Gen_3_22] cases, and that before this Hebrew particle pen, as #Ge 3:22 11:4 [v_Isa_36_8] 42:4 Isa 36:",
    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "Gehazi. [Geha'zi] Servant to the prophet Elisha. He had seen Elisha's miracles, even to the raising of the dead, and yet was tempted to deceive him and fraudulently gain a present from Naaman. He was in consequence smitten with leprosy. In after years he was entertaining the king of Israel with the great works of the prophet, when the Shunammite whose son Elisha had raised to life came to petition the king for her land, and she confirmed the servant's narration. 2 Kings 4: 12-36; 2 Kings 5: 20-27; 2 Kings 8: 4,\n18. Ink, Inkhorn. We know from the papyrus rolls discovered in Egypt that writing with pen, or reed, and ink was practised in early days. Jeremiah caused Baruch to write in a book with ink the denunciations against Israel and Judah. Jer. 36:\n18. The `[group_Canaanites_Gen_10]` horn that contained the ink was carried in the girdle, as it is in some parts of the East to this day. Ezek. 9: 2, 3,\n18. Milk is regarded as such a necessary article of sustenance that it is associated with wine to prefigure that which grace now supplies, without money and without price, and which will be supplied to Israel in a future day. Isa. 55:\n18. Two are to agree in asking. Matt. 18:\n18. Goliath challenged Israel forty days. 1 Sam. 17:\n18. Jehovah swore that the Lord Jesus `[char_Jesus_Ref]` should be a priest for ever after the order of Melchizedek. Ps. 110:\n18. Identified with Tibna, 31 42' N, 35 2' E. Timnath. [Tim'nath]",
    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "is not the \u201cstroke\u201d of Dave Gardner and the scat drummers; the One whose right foot (Matt. 5:35, oh yeah, man) sets the tempo for this dance (Psa. 150:4) strikes in the open (Job 34:26), and those who fall under this \u201cstroke\u201d (vs. 18) are BURIED (Ezek. 24:16). \u201c Will he esteem thy riches? No, not gold...\u201d (vs. 19). \u201cRiches profit not in the day of wrath\u201d (see Prov. 11:4 and comments), and all the forces of strength (vs. 19) who worship the \u201cGod of forces\u201d (Dan. 11:38)\u2014no, it is not \u201cmunitions\u201d silly; the duffers who gave you that guff when they gaffed you delighted in diddling with duds\u2014cannot get a sinner out of Hell once he gets in. You won\u2019t buy off the Judge of Revelation\nverse 18 is not the \u201cstroke\u201d of Dave Gardner and the scat drummers; the One [v_Mat_5_35] whose right foot (Matt. 5:35, oh yeah, man) sets the tempo for this [v_Psa_150_4] dance (Psa. 150:4) strikes in the open (Job 34:26), and those who [v_Ezk_24_16] fall under this \u201cstroke\u201d (vs. 18) are BURIED (Ezek. 24:16). \u201cWill he esteem thy riches? No, not gold...\u201d (vs. 19). [v_Pro_11_4] \u201cRiches profit not in the day of wrath\u201d (see Prov. 11:4 and comments), and all the forces of strength (vs. 19) who worship the [v_Dan_11_38] \u201cGod of forces\u201d (Dan. 11:38)\u2014no, it is not \u201cmunitions\u201d silly; the duffers who gave you that guff when they gaffed you delighted in diddling with duds\u2014cannot get a sinner out of Hell once he gets in. You won\u2019t buy off the Judge of Revelation",
